[2] Maryland
Date: Tue 9 Mar 2021
Source: EquiManagement [abridged, edited]
https://equimanagement.com/news/maryland-reports-two-unrelated-cases-of-neurologic-herpesvirus


Cecil County, Maryland: A horse stabled at a private barn in Cecil County began displaying clinical signs of neurologic equine herpesvirus on Friday [5 Mar 2021]. The horse did not respond to treatment and was euthanized on Saturday [6 Mar 2021]. [This is not the same horse or the same county as the previous story of a horse at Pimlico, Laurel Park, Maryland. - Mod.TG]

Samples from the deceased horse were confirmed positive for neurologic equine herpesvirus on Monday [8 Mar 2021]. The barn has been placed on a hold order, with veterinary professionals monitoring all horses for clinical signs. The hold order will remain in place until all exposed horses have been cleared for release.

[Byline: Kimberly S. Brown]

