[3] Pennsylvania
Date: Tue 9 Mar 2021
Source: The Horse [edited]
https://thehorse.com/197895/pennsylvania-horse-euthanized-due-to-neurologic-ehv-1/


On 3 Mar 2021, an attending veterinarian in Pennsylvania reported a Chester County horse presenting with neurologic signs was suspected with equine herpesvirus-1 (EHV-1). Subsequently, the University of Pennsylvania's large animal hospital, New Bolton Center, in Kennett Square, diagnosed the horse as positive for equine herpesvirus [myeloencephalopathy] (EHM). The horse was euthanized.

An unspecified number of potentially exposed horses have been identified, and New Bolton Center and Pennsylvania Department of Agriculture (PDA) officials are contacting their owners. At this time, this case is unrelated to international travel, transport, or exhibition. New Bolton Center will provide updates as available, in conjunction with PDA.

